  <heading>PACNBIASPPC</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Pointer Authentication Code for return address, using key A, not a Branch Target</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>Pointer Authentication Code for return address, using key A, not a Branch Target. This instruction computes and inserts a pointer authentication code for an instruction address, using two modifiers and key A.</para>
      <para>The address is in X30.</para>
      <para>The first modifier is in SP.</para>
      <para>The second modifier is the 64-bit value of PC.</para>
    </authored>
  </desc>
